Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) offer great promise for the most efficient and cost-effective conversion to electricity of a wide variety of fuels.
Titulo: Promotion on electrochemical performance of a cation deficient SrCo0.7Nb0.1Fe0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cathode materials with high electro-catalytic activity for oxygen reduction reaction is vital to the development of commercially-viable SOFCs to be operated at reduced temperatures.
Titulo: Promotion on electrochemical performance of a cation deficient SrCo0.7Nb0.1Fe0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In present study, cobalt-based perovskite oxides SrxCo0.7Nb0.1Fe0.2O3-delta (SCNF, x = 0.95 and 1) were comparatively investigated as promising cathode materials for intermediate-temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Promotion on electrochemical performance of a cation deficient SrCo0.7Nb0.1Fe0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SCNF compounds with a slight Sr deficiency (S0.95CNF) exhibited single phase of primitive cubic structure with Pm-3m symmetry.
Titulo: Promotion on electrochemical performance of a cation deficient SrCo0.7Nb0.1Fe0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A small Sr deficiency is demonstrated to greatly enhance the electrochemical performance of stoichiometric SCNF cathode due to significantly increased oxygen vacancy.
Titulo: Promotion on electrochemical performance of a cation deficient SrCo0.7Nb0.1Fe0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of S0.95CNF at 700 degrees C was 0.11 Omega cm(2), only about 61% of SCNF.
Titulo: Promotion on electrochemical performance of a cation deficient SrCo0.7Nb0.1Fe0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The rate limiting step for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) is demonstrated to be oxygen ion transfer within the bulk electrode and/or from electrode to electrolyte through the triple phase boundary.
Titulo: Promotion on electrochemical performance of a cation deficient SrCo0.7Nb0.1Fe0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Full cells with the SCNF cathode present good performance and stable output at reduced temperatures, indicating the great potential for enhanced performance of Co-based cathodes with A-site deficiency.
Titulo: Promotion on electrochemical performance of a cation deficient SrCo0.7Nb0.1Fe0.2O3-δ perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
